Governor of Ebonyi State, David Umahi, has ordered that all courts be shut immediately. He gave the directive in a broadcast on Friday. The governor announced that Ebonyi has recorded its first COVID-19 death. He described the development as regrettable and saddening. Umahi ordered all staff of the Judiciary in the state to go for COVID-19 testing. On Thursday, Ebonyi recorded 72 new cases of coronavirus. 